Last week @felipenunesskate received his “signature” legs (for “chilling with friends without getting strange looks”) and then we surprised him with his signature skateboard model the next day. Thanks to @mcop_prosthetics @dupedupe & @davisonbob for helping to create all this magic. Felipe’s groundbreaking video will be out soon at @thrashermag but his pro model is available now at @birdhouseskateboards. The more I get to know him, the more impressed I am with his approach to life and unbreakable determination. No excuses!
🎶: @mrcamcole - “Albion”

node.text:
I got a request from PRK to be a guest singer in their online series, as they inch closer to playing live shows again. Most of their default song selections had been done by the time I was able to participate, but one song stood out: In The City. It was the first song I heard from The Jam, and has always been one of my favorites. Here’s my attempt to channel the prolific @paulwellerhq (who just released a new album!). The ending is my version of a mic/tail drop. Enjoy! 
Thanks @darrinpfeiffer @slee9383 @randybradbury @greghetson @alan_d9000 @900films for doing the heavy lifting on this one.

node.text:
After posting our 1999 doubles run last week, the feedback was incredible. I saw thousands of comments about remembering the event, and a genuine love for that era of skating. The nostalgia was so strong that we decided to do it again yesterday (22 years later). Some of the line was embellished - my 720’s are far less consistent than Andy’s these days - but we tried to match the tricks and the camera angles as best we could. And it just wouldn’t have been complete without the legendary @selema calling the action. Thanks for all of your support through these [many, many] years. We love you, and we still love skating as much as ever.
🎥: @cameronsanchez1 & @katnoaga 
Unrelated (but while you’re here): my NFT is finally dropping in 4/26 via @ethernitychain

node.text:
As a kid that was mostly lambasted for my interest in skateboarding, I never imagined it would be part of the Olympic Games. It’s surreal to now be in Tokyo bearing witness to this milestone in the most unprecedented circumstances. I know in the end it will help to grow skateboarding’s profile internationally, exposing our passion to an audience that has never seen it before or simply refused to embrace it. A whole new generation will get to experience skateboarding with genuine public support and meaningful opportunity. I predict it will be one of the highlights from all of the Olympic Games coverage this year. And I’m here for it. 
	These are clips from earlier today when @paulzitzer and I barged the park course, and then I managed to catch the last 5 minutes of team USA & Japan mens street practice before heading to the NBC set… more to come 🇯🇵🛹📺

node.text: On the eve of my trip to see skateboarding’s debut in the Olympic Games, it is with great pride that I share this news: we will be holding a world class vert contest next month (on my ramp). Vert skating has been unfortunately sidelined recently in the wake of “park” events, but that hasn’t stopped us from pushing limits on the halfpipe, as was exemplified with an insane finals and @gui_khury’s 1080 at @xgames the other day. Vert’s not dead, it’s thriving; come see for yourself. Free to the public. Thanks to @vans & @stateofsport for this opportunity. More info soon. 🛹🌀

node.text:
Crail-cane redemption. Fun fact: @rileyhawk did this trick on miniramps when he was young. I did my first one on vert today… 10 years later.
🎥: @_galina_

My final vert and “street” runs from 1998 B3 (bikes, boards & blades) event at @woodwardcamp. In those years, @xgames had strong viewership so they held a few satellite events throughout the year to keep the hype going. I was just stoked to be skating vert so regularly after a lull in interest and opportunities.
As park (and street) skating takes center stage in the upcoming Tokyo games, I have been working feverishly behind the scenes to bring vert back into the fold of big skate events. Stay tuned.
